Overall this is a high-quality rewrite that correctly modernises the test suite for the current orchestrator architecture. The structural inspection pattern (`declare -f main` + glob matching) is an established convention in this codebase for testing pipeline scripts and is used consistently throughout the sibling test files — no issue there. The behavioral tests (task failure, PR review iterations, end-to-end mock flow) that exercise real functions are well-written and provide meaningful coverage. The five issues above are all minor: three are consistency/clarity problems with the exit-code testing pattern, one is a misleading test name, and one is redundant setup code. None represent correctness failures that would cause the suite to give false positives at runtime, but they should be fixed before the branch is merged to prevent confusing future test authors.
